France Telecom’s Kenya Unit to Cut 400 Jobs, Business Daily Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-05-11T05:29:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/france-telecom-s-kenyan-unit-plans-to-cut-400-jobs-business-daily-reports.html
France Telecom SA (FTE) ’s Kenyan unit plans
to cut 400 jobs in the coming weeks and put billions of
shillings worth of assets up for sale, Business Daily reported,
citing people it didn’t identify.  The measures are being taken by Telkom Kenya to boost cash
reserves and come after revenue fell following a reduction in
mobile-phone call rates, the Nairobi-based newspaper said.  Telkom Kenya spokeswoman Angela Ng’ang’a-Mumo wasn’t
immediately available for comment when Bloomberg News called the
company today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  